    {
        "question_html": "<p><span class=\"english\">Write a paragraph on</span><span class=\"english\"> “</span><span class=\"english\">Importance of Adolescent Population</span><span class=\"english\">” </span><span class=\"english\">within 10 sentences.</span><span> </span></p>",
        "options_html": [],
        "correct_answer_html": null,
        "solution_html": "<p><span class=\"english\">Importance of Adolescent Population</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">The adolescent population is key to determining the future of any society. Adolescents are at a stage of life where they are developing important skills, both intellectually and socially. They are the future workforce and will contribute to the economy in many ways. Their health, education, and well-being are essential for the progress of nations. Investing in the adolescent population through education and healthcare can create a generation that is better equipped to face future challenges. As they transition into adulthood, their decisions and behaviors will impact society as a whole. Adolescents also bring fresh ideas and innovations, and driving change in technology, culture, and society. Supporting this age group helps reduce poverty and inequalities and ensures more equal opportunities for everyone. Adolescents are also more open to social and environmental changes, which makes them key players in promoting sustainability and social justice. In summary, nurturing and protecting the adolescent population is crucial for any nation.</span></p><p><span> </span></p><p><span class=\"english\">Marks Distribution:</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">Highest Mark ---------------------------------------------------------------------09 Marks </span></p><p><span class=\"english\">(</span><span class=\"english\">i</span><span class=\"english\">) For Title (</span><span class=\"english\">Importance of Adolescent Population</span><span class=\"english\">) </span><span class=\"english\">---------------------------------</span><span class=\"english\">01</span><span> </span><span class=\"english\">Mark</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">(ii) Topic Sentence (Introduction)</span><span class=\"english\"> ---------------------------------------------</span><span class=\"english\">01 Mark</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">The adolescent population plays a crucial role in shaping the future of any society.</span></p><p><span> </span><span class=\"english\">(iii) Context Explanation (</span><span class=\"english\">Adolescent Development and Economic Contribution</span><span class=\"english\">)</span><span class=\"english\"> (Any 6) ----06 Marks</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">• Adolescents are developing intellectual and social skills. </span><span class=\"english\"><br/>‎• They are the future workforce and contribute to the economy. </span><span class=\"english\"><br/>‎• Their health, education, and well-being are crucial for nation's progress. </span><span class=\"english\"><br/>‎• Investing in adolescents through education and healthcare can equip them for future challenges. </span><span class=\"english\"><br/>‎• Adolescents bring fresh ideas and innovation, driving technological, cultural, and societal changes. </span><span class=\"english\"><br/>‎• Supporting this age group reduces poverty and inequalities, ensuring equal opportunities. </span><span class=\"english\"><br/>‎• Adolescents promote sustainability and social justice.</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">(iv) Conclusion --------------------------------------------------------01 Mark </span></p><p><span class=\"english\">In summary, nurturing and protecting the adolescent population is crucial for any nation.</span></p><p><span> </span></p><p><span class=\"english\">Instructions:</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">1. </span><span class=\"english\">For every 3 spelling/grammatical mistakes, 01 mark has to be deducted.</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">2</span><span class=\"english\">. We will consider up to 12 sentences. However, if a student writes more than 12 sentences but less than double (20 sentences), 50% of the deserving marks must be deducted. If it becomes double (20 sentences), full marks have to be deducted. </span><span class=\"english\">Comment: Write within 10 sentences.</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">3. </span><span class=\"english\">Students must write within a para. If a student writes more than one para, half of the deserving marks must be deducted. </span><span class=\"english\">(Comment: Write within single/one para)</span><span class=\"english\">.</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">4.</span><span class=\"english\"> For writing only the title of the paragraph bears no mark.</span></p>"
    },
    {
        "question_html": "<p><span class=\"english\">Make meaningful sentences with the following words/phrase.</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">Huntsman</span><span class=\"english\">, </span><span class=\"english\">Dismay</span><span class=\"english\">, </span><span class=\"english\">Pertaining</span><span class=\"english\">, </span><span class=\"english\">Hemorrhage</span><span class=\"english\">, </span><span class=\"english\">Sweet company</span></p>",
        "options_html": [],
        "correct_answer_html": null,
        "solution_html": "<p><span class=\"english\">Huntsman = The </span><span class=\"english\">huntsman</span><span class=\"english\"> ventured deep into the forest in search of game.</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">Dismay ( Noun ) = </span><span class=\"english\">Dismay</span><span class=\"english\"> swept across her face when she realized she had forgotten her important documents at home.</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">Dismay ( Verb ) = Their reaction dismayed him.  [Since dismayed is used here as the past form of the verb, dismayed can also be used as  an adjective but this form of the word violates the corresponding parts of speech. Hence, dismayed using as adjective won’t be acceptable.]</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">Pertaining = There are many laws </span><span class=\"english\">pertaining</span><span class=\"english\"> to the protection of children from early marriage.</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">Hemorrhage = </span><span class=\"english\">Hemorrhage</span><span class=\"english\"> is a serious risk during childbirth for young girls who marry early.</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">Sweet company = He loves to keep </span><span class=\"english\">sweet company</span><span class=\"english\"> around him all the time.</span></p><p><span> </span></p><p><a></a><span class=\"english\">Instructions</span><span class=\"english\">:</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">(</span><span class=\"english\">i</span><span class=\"english\">)</span><span class=\"english\"> Any correct and logically meaningful sentence will be accepted. </span><span class=\"english\">(Sentences with weak meaning will not be allowed.)</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">(ii)</span><span class=\"english\"> For any grammatical or structural mistake, full marks have to be deducted. Examiners have to show and correct the mistake(s) in the scripts.</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">(iii)</span><span class=\"english\"> For </span><span class=\"english\">02</span><span class=\"english\"> spelling mistakes, </span><span class=\"english\">01 mark</span><span class=\"english\"> will be deducted, for </span><span class=\"english\">01 spelling</span><span class=\"english\"> mistake, </span><span class=\"english\">0.5 marks</span><span class=\"english\"> will be deducted from that very sentence.</span><span class=\"english\"><br/>‎</span><span class=\"english\">(iv)</span><span class=\"english\"> For changing the part of speech of the given word by adding a </span><span class=\"english\">suffix or prefix</span><span class=\"english\">, the full marks have to be deducted from the very number. But students can use any form if the given word is a verb (depending on the </span><span class=\"english\">subject-verb agreement, tense, person, number</span><span class=\"english\">, etc.)</span><span class=\"english\"><br/>‎</span><span class=\"english\">Comment: </span><span class=\"english\">Use the given word without changing its parts of speech</span><span class=\"english\">.</span></p>"
    },
    {
        "question_html": "<p><span class=\"english\">Explain the following stanza: </span></p><p><span class=\"english\">“But to go to school in a summer morn,-</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">O it drives all joy away!</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">Under a cruel eye outworn,</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">The little ones spend the day</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">In sighing and dismay.”</span></p>",
        "options_html": [],
        "correct_answer_html": null,
        "solution_html": "<p><span class=\"english\">In this stanza from \"The Schoolboy,\" the speaker contrasts the natural beauty of a summer morning with the harsh reality of school. The very idea of attending school during such a pleasant time \"drives all joy away,\" replacing happiness with a sense of dread. The classroom is described as being under a \"cruel eye outworn,\" suggesting a weary and oppressive authority figure who dominates the students. The children themselves are portrayed as suffering, spending their day in a state of \"sighing and dismay\" instead of learning with enthusiasm. This stanza thus highlights the profound unhappiness and emotional burden that institutional education places upon young children.</span></p><p><span> </span></p><p><span class=\"english\">Marks Distribution:</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">Highest</span><span> </span><span class=\"english\">Mark</span><span class=\"english\">--------------------------------------</span><span class=\"english\">05 Marks</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">(A) Identification of the Quote and Source </span><span class=\"english\">---------</span><span class=\"english\">01 Mark </span></p><p><span class=\"english\">• </span><span class=\"english\">In this stanza is taken from William Blake's poem \"The Schoolboy”.</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">(B) Context Explanation (</span><span class=\"english\">From Joy to Dismay: The Burden of Schooling</span><span class=\"english\">) </span><span class=\"english\">(</span><span class=\"english\">Any</span><span> </span><span class=\"english\">4 Points</span><span class=\"english\">)---</span><span class=\"english\">04 Marks</span><span> </span></p><p><span class=\"english\">• Contrasts the beauty of summer with the harsh reality of school. </span><span class=\"english\"><br/>‎• School attendance replaces joy with dread. </span><span class=\"english\"><br/>‎• Classroom depicted as oppressive, with a \"cruel eye outworn.\" </span><span class=\"english\"><br/>‎• Children depicted as suffering, not learning enthusiastically. </span><span class=\"english\"><br/>‎• Highlights the emotional burden of institutional education on young children.</span></p><p><span> </span></p><p><span class=\"english\">Instructions</span><span class=\"english\">:</span><span> </span></p><p><span class=\"english\">**For every 03 spelling or grammatical errors, 01 mark has to be deducted. However, mistakes regarding capital and small letters can be overlooked.</span><span> </span></p>"
    }
